<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Definitely I continued reading it - the descriptions of the relationships are excellent and I certainly appreciated that part of his writings and, as <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Definitely I continued reading it - the descriptions of the relationships are excellent and I certainly appreciated that part of his writings and, as you point out, particularly the world from the point of view of a 6 year-old. Like I noted, what becomes "heavy" with James Agee is when he wanders into disclosing all that is going on in his mind - all the phylosophizing that doesn't really add (in my opinion) to the his "story".<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
